            <h2>Lauda Europe Airlines Refund Policy</h2>

            <p>Lauda was previously known as Amira air, a low-budget Austrian airline. It started its operation as Lauda in 2018 with two main bases, the Palma de Mallorca Airport and the Vienna International Airport. Lauda Airlines now works as a west lease and charter services for Raynier, other clients, and third parties. </p>
            <p>This means they don't have a fixed destination as they work for themselves but Raynier and third-party clients. There is only economy class available in these aircraft and has facilities like good food, onboard Wi-Fi and many more. </p>
            <h2>Refund Policy </h2>
            <p>Lauda does not have any <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/refund-policy.aspx">refund policy</a> of its own. But as it is an EU-based company, it has to abide by the law of EC261. The law of EC261 states that if certain conditions are met, you will get compensation for your canceled flight by the airline company. If you had a flight from Eu, you canceled the flight at least 14 hours before the takeoff, and if the flight is late at least for a minimum of 3 hours, you are entitled to get the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/lauda-europe-airlines-refund-policy.aspx">refund from Lauda</a>. </p>
            <h3>Frequently asked question</h3>
            <h3>Who can receive a refund with Lauda Airlines? </h3>
            <p>If you meet the conditions mentioned above, you will receive the refund/compensation in the mode of payment that you used to book the flight ticket. If you used your debit card or your credit card, then the refund money would reflect in it within 2 days, or if you used cash, you would be paid in cash. </p>
            <h3>How can I cancel a flight ticket with Lauda Airlines? </h3>
            <p>If you have booked a ticket from a travel agency, you need to visit them and get your ticket canceled along with your refund, but it may be according to the rules and regulations of the travel agency. If you booked the ticket from any website, you can directly visit the website and cancel it. It might take a maximum of 7 days to get your refund money in your bank account. </p>
            <h3>Where can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p>If you used your debit card or your credit card, then the refund money would reflect in it within 2 days, or if you used cash, you would be paid in cash. </p>
            <h3>Will I get any compensation from Lauda airlines if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p>If you booked the ticket from any website, you can directly visit the website and cancel it. It might take 7 days to get your refund money in your bank account. No, you won't receive any refund if your flight is delayed by 2 hours. </p>
            <h3>Is my flight refundable? </h3>
            <p>You might get a refund if you cancel your plane ticket at the latest 14 hours before the flight or take off for some unforeseen situation. The other reasons could be if the flight is either too late or canceled by the airline's authorities. </p>
